<TITLE> Chief adviser sends message of condolence </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 27 (bdnews24.com)Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed expressed sorrow Wednesday at the demise of 'Sangbad' editor Bazlur Rahman. In a message of condolence, Fakhruddin said Rahman was a beacon of Bangladesh journalism and lived the example of utmost dedication to the profession. The death of this progressive professional has caused irreparable loss, not only to the newspaper he served for almost five decades, but also to his country, the chief adviser said. Fakhruddin also recalled Bazlur Rahman's heroic role in the War of Liberation in which he fought so bravely. He offered prayers for the deceased, and sent condolences to his family on their bereavement. bdnews
